        "id": 4098330,
        "name": "Dylan P",
        "username": "Dylan_P",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dylan_p/{size}/100235_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-06-21T07:29:04.482Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019ve got some of my 2018 Bindis left that I want to compare to Giaconda.</p>\n<p>Is it worth the effort? The Kostas and Quartz are top notch; but the Giaconda seems near impossible on availability, with the only USA WS listing on Cask Cartel at $700-800 the past few months <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/face_vomiting.png?v=12\" title=\":face_vomiting:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":face_vomiting:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\">\u2026 Can\u2019t imagine any major import to US based on the exclusivity and domestic demand in AUS, but if anyone has advice on acquiring a bottle in the US would be much appreciated!</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2023-06-21T07:29:04.482Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
